title: Gebel es-Silsilah
description: A mountain on the west bank of the Nile 40 miles north of Aswan with over 30 18th dynasty shrines. This site was first settled in the late Predynastic period, wan important sandstone quarry in the 18th dynasty with some inhabitants, and was still in use in the Roman period.
